A tragic incident unfolded as an Adam Air plane crashed in Indonesia's West Sulawesi province, claiming the lives of at least 90 individuals.
Among the passengers were three Americans, identified as Scott Jackson, Stephanie, and Lindsay.
The aircraft, carrying 102 people, disappeared between Java and Sulawesi islands.
Rescue efforts were hindered by stormy weather, with only 12 survivors located.
Indonesian officials criticized the delayed response in deploying search teams.
The cause of the crash remains unknown, with concerns raised about the plane's altitude.
International condolences poured in, highlighting the devastating impact of the disaster.
